flowchart TD
    A[POST /api/agents/run\nTrigger: src/backend/routers/agent.py::runtime_agent_run] -->|RuntimeAgentRunRequest\nquery + optional thread_id/user_id/checkpoint_id\nWhy: execute one agent run| B[src/backend/services/agent_service.py::run_runtime_agent]

    B -->|Trigger: AgentFactory.create_langgraph_agent + LangGraphAgentScaffold.run\nData: payload + db session\nWhy: execute retrieval/validation/synthesis pipeline| C[src/backend/agents/langgraph_agent.py::LangGraphAgentScaffold.run]

    C -->|Data returned: output + thread_id + checkpoint_id + graph_state.execution.persistence\nWhy: expose resolved persistence state for API + tracing| B

    B -->|Trigger: _extract_persistence_context(payload, graph_result)\nData: thread_id, resolved_checkpoint_id/checkpoint_id, user_id\nWhy: ensure trace includes deepAgent persistence identifiers| D[metadata.persistence_context]

    B -->|Trigger: _start_agent_span(...).span.update(...)\nData: query input, output response, agent identity, retrieval/validation + persistence_context\nWhy: one span per run at execution boundary| E[Langfuse span: agent.run]

    E -->|When tracing disabled\nTrigger: LangfuseTracingHandle.start_as_current_span returns no-op context\nWhy: preserve existing API behavior with zero tracing side effects| F[No external tracing calls]

    N1[Tradeoff: checkpoint_id in span metadata prefers\nexecution.persistence.resolved_checkpoint_id over request echo\nfor fidelity to effective checkpoint state.]:::note
    D -. decision .-> N1

    N2[Tradeoff: user_id falls back to "anonymous" when omitted\nso persistence context stays explicit and deterministic in traces.]:::note
    D -. decision .-> N2

    classDef note fill:#f7f7e8,stroke:#8a8a6a,color:#222;
